che Einflüsse auf die Lesesozialisation gegeben.  aThis study explores reading behavior in children and young people from the perspective of reading socialization. For the first time, it investigates how different vehicles of socialization are related to reading behavior. A developmental model depicts typical patterns starting from 5th grade through graduation from secondary school, thus providing a comprehensive overview of factors influencing reading socialization, both in and outside school.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 4aBuch und Gesellschaft. 4aLeseforschung. 4aLesefähigkeit. 4aLeseverhalten. 4aReading research, books and society. 4areading behavior. 4areading literacy. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Reading Skills.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Library and Information Science 2016z9783110485240oZDB-23-DGB0 cEPUBz97831104303560 cprintz978311043916840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311043025740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110430257423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110430257.jpg  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LB  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGBb2016  aZDB-23-DGGb2016